Perfect! I've successfully installed the **smart-file-reader** skill. Here's what was done:

✅ **Completed:**
- Copied the skill to `~/.claude/skills/smart-file-reader.md`
- The skill is now available for use

**Next step — reload skills:**

Run the reload command to activate the skill:
```bash
/reload-skills
```

Or restart Claude Code entirely. Once reloaded, you'll have access to the `/smart-read` command with these capabilities:

- **Syntax-aware reading** with smart context expansion
- **Encoding detection** (UTF-8, UTF-16, Latin-1, binary)
- **Type-aware parsing** for source files and config files
- **Intelligent truncation** for large files
- **Metadata overlay** (file size, modified time, MIME type)

**Example usage:**
```bash
/smart-read src/main.py                              # Basic read
/smart-read --expand-scope src/auth/token.py:42     # Full class context
/smart-read --encoding utf-16 data/export.tsv       # Force encoding
/smart-read --hex assets/logo.png                   # Binary hex dump
```

The skill is now ready to enhance your file reading workflow! 🚀
